From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <dpaa1@vyos-ls1046a-build>
Date: Tue, 10 Jun 2026 14:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa: ethtool ntuple -> FMan CC static-tree bridge (M3-3b
 production consumer)

The fman_cc_tree_install() consumer API (0098/0106/0108) had no
production caller - only the 0107 debugfs test harness. This patch adds
the standard-kernel-interface bridge so userspace can drive FMan
exact-match flow steering through ethtool ntuple (rxnfc), mirroring the
0104 ingress-policer pattern (userspace -> standard kernel tool ->
driver bridge):

  ethtool -N ethX flow-type udp4 src-ip A dst-ip B dst-port P \
          action <queue> loc <prio>

The vyos-1x 'set system offload classify' CLI (vyos-1x-026) is the
config-mode consumer that emits these ethtool invocations on commit.

What this adds
--------------
- dpaa_ethtool.c: .get_rxnfc/.set_rxnfc. ETHTOOL_SRXCLSRLINS/SRXCLSRLDEL
  accumulate per-port rules (struct dpaa_cls_rule, sorted by location =
  match priority, lowest wins); every mutation rebuilds the port's
  static CC tree via fman_cc_tree_destroy() + fman_cc_tree_install()
  (the 0106 install -> get_base -> KGSE_CCBS-graft sequence; destroy
  detaches the graft before freeing MURAM so silicon never walks a
  stale tree - the brief steering gap falls back to the RSS path).
  ETHTOOL_GRXCLSRLCNT/GRXCLSRULE/GRXCLSRLALL give `ethtool -n`
  visibility; GRXRINGS reports DPAA_ETH_PCD_RXQ_NUM. A failed install
  on rule insert rolls the rule list back so software state matches
  silicon.

- action semantics: the ethtool queue index [0..DPAA_ETH_PCD_RXQ_NUM)
  selects the Nth FQ_TYPE_RX_PCD frame queue on priv->dpaa_fq_list; the
  FQ's QMan channel determines the servicing CPU - the spec sec 5.4
  "HW classifier -> right RX FQ -> right CPU" semantic. The resolved
  FQID is carried in fman_cc_key.target_fqid so the 0108 leaf encoder
  emits the real RM 8.7.4.3 hardware enqueue-AD. RX_CLS_FLOW_DISC
  (drop) is rejected (-EOPNOTSUPP, no drop leaf encoding).

- validation (documented limits, not silent): flow-type tcp4/udp4 only;
  each field mask all-ones or all-zero (the CC record is exact-match -
  no prefixes); at least one field must participate; at most
  FMAN_CC_MAX_STATIC_KEYS (32) rules per port; location < 32 (or
  RX_CLS_LOC_ANY -> lowest free). The KG-emitted compare key carries no
  protocol byte (0108), so tcp4/udp4 rules with identical address/port
  tuples match the SAME traffic - accepted, documented in the block
  comment. Set-side gated on FMAN_CAP_CC_EXACT_MATCH so non-210-ucode
  boards reject with -EOPNOTSUPP at the first ethtool call.

- dpaa_eth.h: cls_rules/cls_rule_cnt/cls_tree_installed on dpaa_priv
  (mutated only under rtnl - the rxnfc entry points); dpaa_cls_flush()
  declaration.

- dpaa_eth.c: INIT_LIST_HEAD(&priv->cls_rules) at probe;
  dpaa_cls_flush() in dpaa_remove() (detaches the graft + frees the
  tree before the FQs it steers to are freed).

Native arm64 compile of drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/{dpaa,fman}/
with LOCALVERSION=-vyos: 0 warnings / 0 errors.

Spec sec 5.4 (M3-3b production consumer).

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <dpaa1@vyos-ls1046a-build>
---
